# BROWSER-notifications.md - Medium Notification & Reply Detection Patterns

## § 1. Extract Notifications

Page: `https://medium.com/me/notifications` (embed 3s wait in evaluate)

Only returns actionable types (response + note). Follows/subscribes/claps filtered out in JS.

```javascript
browser.act({
  kind: "evaluate",
  fn: `async () => {
    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 3000));
    const tabpanel = document.querySelector('div[role="tabpanel"]');
    if (!tabpanel) return { count: 0, items: [] };
    const notifications = Array.from(tabpanel.children);
    const items = [];
    for (let i = 0; i < notifications.length && items.length < 10; i++) {
      const n = notifications[i];
      const text = n.innerText;
      const isResponse = text.includes('responded');
      const isNote = text.includes('left a note');
      if (!isResponse && !isNote) continue;
      const author = text.split('\\n')[0] || '';
      if (author.toLowerCase().includes('{{handle}}')) continue;
      const links = Array.from(n.querySelectorAll('a'));
      const aLink = links.find(a => a.href.includes('/p/'));
      items.push({
        type: isResponse ? 'response' : 'note',
        author: author.slice(0, 40),
        articleUrl: aLink ? aLink.href.split('?')[0] : ''
      });
    }
    return { count: items.length, items };
  }`,
  profile: "{{browser_profile}}"
})
```

