## § 2. Check Already Replied (browse_and_engage only — NOT for notifications)

🚨 False-positives on notification pages (our original comment has `/@{{handle}}` link). Use tracking file dedup for notifications.

```javascript
browser.act({
  kind: "evaluate",
  fn: `async () => {
    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 3000));
    // Only works on regular articles — NOT on notification response pages
    const {{handle}}Links = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('a[href*="/@{{handle}}"]'))
      .filter(a => !a.href.includes('sidebar_menu'));
    const hasOurComment = {{handle}}Links.length > 0 ||
                          /\\nYou\\n\\n\\d+\\s+(mins?|hours?|days?)\\s+ago/.test(document.body.innerText);
    return {
      alreadyCommented: hasOurComment,
      {{handle}}LinksCount: {{handle}}Links.length
    };
  }`,
  profile: "{{browser_profile}}"
})
```
